Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.96,0:00:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! The twins are playing again!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:14.75,0:00:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:16.68,0:00:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.09,0:00:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Together, they're our head girls! {from the book, probably means top dogs of their school; seito kaicho = presidents of the student council!}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:20.19,0:00:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The pride of our school... {gakuen no hokori?}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:22.12,0:00:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The O’Sullivan twins!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:24.83,0:00:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Go for it, Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:26.31,0:00:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I got this, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:29.63,0:00:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning set!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:32.00,0:00:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Patricia and Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:35.14,0:00:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You won this one.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.67,0:00:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.21,0:00:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hear this! {taihen yo?}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:44.61,0:00:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess what, Pat! Redroof\Nhas picked you as its top athlete!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:49.90,0:00:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:51.32,0:00:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't act so surprised. {lit: you had confidence, didn't you}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:54.18,0:00:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat’s good at every sport—\Nafter all, she’s captain of the hockey team! {sounds like pokkei}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:57.78,0:00:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.26,0:01:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's not all.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.46,0:01:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel’s been chosen for the School’s Honor Roll Award, too!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:05.70,0:01:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:08.07,0:01:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,She topped every graduation exam but geography.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:12.47,0:01:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? And who topped geography?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.81,0:01:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, of course! {I hate them already}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:17.48,0:01:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are simply perfect!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:19.41,0:01:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a shame you have to graduate \Nand leave us so soon... {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:30.66,0:01:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, everyone! Thanks a lot!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.57,0:01:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't study in this classroom ever again.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.87,0:01:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Giving it our best in sports...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.61,0:01:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Giving it our best in studying...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.91,0:01:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, this school life was unforgettable.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.10,0:01:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.21,0:01:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was supposed to only get better from here... {their parents chose to transfer them to another school}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.98,0:01:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It really was.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.78,0:01:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.92,0:02:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we, of all people,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.02,0:02:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,have to transfer to that stupid school?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.12,0:02:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Clare's...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.33,0:02:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is a disaster of a school!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.16,0:02:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How can such folly...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.69,0:02:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,ever be forgiven? {more specifically "doing something like that to us... unforgivable!"}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.00,0:02:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we go to that school \Nif we don't want to?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.26,0:04:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready? We're going in.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.31,0:04:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.38,0:04:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.78,0:04:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to talk!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.25,0:04:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Isabel, Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.72,0:04:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like you to call off this whole idea \Nof us transferring to St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.33,0:04:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.79,0:04:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, so it's about that?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.28,0:04:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We're serious, Father!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.83,0:04:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone says that St. Clare's \Nis a terrible school!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.84,0:04:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a plain, boorish school.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.87,0:04:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They let in just about anyone, \Neven if they're not from a good family.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.79,0:04:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All the students there \Nwear torn clothes day after day. {Reworded to be less clunky}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.94,0:04:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Both Pat and I are outstanding students.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.98,0:04:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we deserve a better school.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.25,0:04:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, for example,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.19,0:04:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ringmere School.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.82,0:04:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's famous for only letting in rich and bright girls.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.22,0:04:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They have expensive desks imported from Paris.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.93,0:04:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to wear an evening dress for dinner.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.98,0:05:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All the girls in our class \Nwill go to Ringmere School.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.33,0:05:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Clare's pales in comparison...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.14,0:05:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, you two—\Ndid all that studying up to now
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.99,0:05:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just teach you how to talk so stuck-up?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.68,0:05:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.34,0:05:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Clare's is a wonderful and sensible school.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.62,0:05:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the Head personally, \Nand I like her a lot.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.02,0:05:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But if we transfer to St. Clare’s, we’ll be newcomers, \Nwho are also at the bottom of the ladder! {probably means the lowest in age, as in that school only accepts girls from 14 through 18 or something; never clarified in the book}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.76,0:05:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the local stars at Redroofs!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.26,0:05:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the head girl and the hockey team captain.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.90,0:05:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d much rather go to Ringmere with everyone else and keep the popularity I’ve got now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.68,0:05:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s pretty clear St. Clare’s doesn’t set the bar very high when it comes to studying.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.12,0:05:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of place doesn't suit us, \Nexemplary students!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.45,0:05:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't go to St. Clare's!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.16,0:05:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Crying like babies—\Nhow old do you think you are?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.87,0:05:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.84,0:05:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You two were spoiled and got full of yourselves, \Neven though you’re really nothing special.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.72,0:05:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That's not true!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.53,0:06:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We only say that because we really are...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.56,0:06:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, you two.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.28,0:06:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to become humble and kind daughters I can be proud of,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.64,0:06:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you will cheer up and start over \Nfrom scratch at your new school.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.64,0:06:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That really is the thing \Nyou two need the most right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.98,0:06:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, go back to your room \Nand reflect on what you just said.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.54,0:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Clare's...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.17,0:06:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is the worst.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.49,0:06:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad and Mum don't understand us at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.46,0:06:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in the slightest.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.63,0:06:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must children do what adults say forever?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.13,0:06:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There are things that children understand way better than adults.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.79,0:06:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But now it's decided...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.54,0:06:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never forget the feelings I have tonight. \NA school like St. Clare's...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.38,0:06:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never agree \Nto a school such as St. Clare's!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.29,0:07:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, Isabel, that's the special train to St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.30,0:07:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we get on that, \Nwe'll become students of St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.89,0:07:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.39,0:07:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can't take it anymore!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.78,0:07:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This lame uniform is killing me!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.08,0:07:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And this lacrosse stick… \NI wish we were still playing hockey.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.79,0:07:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a disaster...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.22,0:07:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, we're made to wear...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.86,0:07:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the same uniform as them. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.33,0:07:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you two still mumbling about? \NYou need to get on! {''both'' just... fels clunky here to me}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.44,0:07:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.60,0:07:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, she's so elegant!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.64,0:07:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing like St. Clare's students!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.77,0:07:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? And you two must be the O'Sullivan twins.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.36,0:07:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.98,0:07:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Patricia, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.06,0:08:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.38,0:08:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.86,0:08:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.42,0:08:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as the letter said.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.32,0:08:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you Miss Roberts of St. Clare's?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.55,0:08:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.64,0:08:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.16,0:08:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's your "Hello"?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.14,0:08:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hello.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.26,0:08:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.20,0:08:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.26,0:08:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts, I know they can be a bit selfish sometimes, but please be patient with them.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.64,0:08:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I believe they both have it in them \Nto grow into wonderful ladies.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.04,0:08:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, say your goodbyes to your mother now.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.51,0:08:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The train leaves in two minutes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.65,0:08:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you settle into St. Clare’s dorm, \NI won’t be seeing either of you for a good while.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.95,0:08:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to miss you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.22,0:08:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.29,0:08:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been harsh at times too, but only because I care about your spiritual growth. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.26,0:08:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up and stay strong.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.49,0:08:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna write you letters.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.43,0:08:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.51,0:09:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No one here knows us.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.73,0:09:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I totally wouldn't be able to stand it on my own. {/if I were alone}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.41,0:09:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing we have each other. {lit: thank god we're twins}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.98,0:09:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, sandwiches, everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.25,0:09:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have ginger ale, lemonade, and black tea.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.52,0:09:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the lunch is here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.59,0:09:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my. Sorry, little one. Newcomer? {New student}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.86,0:09:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.63,0:09:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Your tie is undone.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.21,0:09:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I got your lunch as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.58,0:09:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.76,0:09:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go, little one.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.57,0:09:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she really say that? {little one}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.40,0:09:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s from the top class. {in age}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.11,0:09:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Next to you lower-class kids, \Nshe’s practically an adult. {/newcomers}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.65,0:09:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We were in the top class ourselves \Nat our previous school!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:42.32,0:09:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And head girls to boot.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.05,0:09:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, I've made up my mind, you hear?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.47,0:09:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. I'll do the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.99,0:09:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.89,0:09:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! We're twins, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.23,0:09:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't let anyone look down on us!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.30,0:09:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Seniors or whatever, \Nthey'll all look at us as equals!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.93,0:10:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No kowtowing to anyone! {lit: we won't become familiar with anyone - meaning "we won't let anyone treat us as their buddy who they can boss around"}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.30,0:10:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No laughing at us! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.67,0:10:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll never become just {\i1}two of{\i0} \NSt. Clare's students! {lit: we'll never get along with something like clare}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.00,0:10:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.47,0:10:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! Don't tell me—are you two twins?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.01,0:10:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems so.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.01,0:10:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so alike it feels surreal! {lit: that resemblance is like a joke}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.05,0:10:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And who might you be?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.08,0:10:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet we're in the same class.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.65,0:10:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We've heard about two new girls coming.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.48,0:10:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so thrilled! I’ve never met twins before. \NPleased to meet you, Surreal Twins. {joke-like again; -chan = diminuitive}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.23,0:10:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.09,0:10:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do all St. Clare's students babble like you?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.23,0:10:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it quite right—\Nwe're {\i1}so{\i0} alike, it almost feels surreal! {this translation of like a joke is getting out of hand}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.87,0:10:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that means we also share this desire not to talk to you!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.31,0:10:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're surreal, aren't we?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.27,0:10:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That means riding in the same car as you is making us sick!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:44.44,0:10:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you would excuse us...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.53,0:10:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.28,0:10:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! They're the worst!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.69,0:11:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my Isabel. \NThat line earlier was spot-on.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.93,0:11:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's keep this up.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.37,0:11:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So awfully rural! {lit: incredible countryside - meaning as opposed to urban}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.04,0:11:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we're going to take the bus to school now.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.54,0:11:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.15,0:11:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What an awful country road!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.59,0:11:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, I can't take this for much longer! {lit: how long does it continue}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.66,0:11:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be able to see St. Clare's building soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.23,0:11:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the school where you’ll be spending \Nthe next seven years. {a bit long considering they were 14 at this point in the book, but maybe they're a bit younger in the anime, an opposite of what happened to luise and lotte lol; either way this school is supposed to only have 6 grades so idk what this is about}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.57,0:11:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your friends, teachers, and school building—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.48,0:11:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,everything you will think, worry, and grow with \Nfor the many years to come—is at that school.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.83,0:11:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No way am I going down without a fight! {lit: I'm definitely not being quiet or something - means "I'll raise hell for sure"}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.25,0:12:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Just you watch. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.87,0:12:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not as bad as I thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.38,0:12:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just big and empty—\Nlike some hospital, really!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.55,0:12:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, Isabel,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.30,0:12:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hillary will give you a tour of the school.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.55,0:12:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s the head girl of your new class. {not exactly seito kaicho from before}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.46,0:12:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Hilary Wentworth. Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.08,0:12:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,O'Sullivan twins. Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.06,0:12:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is our grand hall, \Nwhere we also hold the religious services. {/auditorium}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.76,0:13:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.47,0:13:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, isn't it breathtaking?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.45,0:13:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Nothing special!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.85,0:13:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our study room. {jishushitsu is supposed to be "(private) study room" so idk how this works}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.40,0:13:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You do it in all this racket?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.87,0:13:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We all had a private study at our previous school.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.31,0:13:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You had all the time in the world \Nto read on your own.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.71,0:13:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Here at St. Clare's, only the top form \Ngirls get a private study. {no clue what's this yasai, could be yasen = contest, but there's no contest that I know of here; in book it was "At their old school they had shared a fine study between them, but here there were no studies except for the top form girls and the fifth form." so it's probably this somehow; also I guess form is the british word for grade?}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.28,0:13:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as we thought—\Nwe really don't belong in a place like this. {lit: shouldn't have come - but not like they had any say in it}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.02,0:13:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.47,0:13:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But in return, we get to do some fun things \Ntogether in this common study room.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.97,0:13:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? What kind of things?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.47,0:13:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you. This way.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.62,0:13:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.92,0:13:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.78,0:13:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The third book from the right \Nholds a secret message from our class.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.95,0:13:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,News!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.04,0:14:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A mole on Miss Roberts' nape! \N(Is it) a token for "boyfriend wanted"?! {no quotes originally but they're implied ig}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.18,0:14:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Isabel, I’ve been meaning to say—\Nyou kind of remind me of Miss Roberts.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.70,0:14:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.70,0:14:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With your bright eyes, \Nand your kindness.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.19,0:14:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You really think so?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.42,0:14:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you forget our vow?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.92,0:14:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I only smiled a little—just on one cheek, is all! {literal, think she means by that that it wasn't a profound smile, just responding to hilary's nicety}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.36,0:14:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You must stay on your guard! {lit: don't make your mind/feelings go loose}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.23,0:14:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, you two?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.70,0:14:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.23,0:14:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hillary, it looks like they've started checking the belongings of new students into the dorms.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.00,0:14:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.41,0:14:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go see the Matron at once. {from the book; ryobo = housemother; dorm mother}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.61,0:14:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,She's like a strict but kind mother to all of us.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.42,0:14:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia and Isabel O'Sullivan, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.75,0:14:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.72,0:14:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother must be really meticulous.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.09,0:14:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s folded all your sheets \Nand dresses for outings so neatly.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.49,0:14:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, our mum's the best.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.75,0:15:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, though, you’ll be the ones mending any socks or clothes you tear.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.75,0:15:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.70,0:15:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ourselves?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.90,0:15:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.51,0:15:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't do that!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.97,0:15:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There were sewing maids \Nat our other school to do that!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.03,0:15:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that's shocking!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.21,0:15:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are no sewing maids here.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.78,0:15:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So be careful with your things, and remember that they cost your parents money.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.25,0:15:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our parents aren’t that tight-fisted! If we rip something, they’ll just buy us a new one right away.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.53,0:15:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness me! There’s one thing I can’t bear, \Nand that’s carelessness and waste!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.40,0:15:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you’re at St. Clare’s, \Nyou’d better get that through your heads.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.32,0:15:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... How did it go?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.32,0:15:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.21,0:15:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She's awful!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.11,0:15:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She's no "mother." {Matron}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.58,0:15:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,More like a terrible cantankerous grandma.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.31,0:15:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.80,0:15:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you—those twins are the worst.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.30,0:15:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never accept them as my roommates.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.69,0:15:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And what are you going to do? {about it}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.80,0:15:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I have this to help me.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.62,0:15:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.26,0:15:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A mop?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.07,0:16:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But... What do you mean? {/what will you do}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.39,0:16:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop it on them, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.50,0:16:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds like a splendid welcome.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.08,0:16:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The shower room is at the end of the hall, \Nthe dining room is on the first floor.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.36,0:16:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is Room 7, our room.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.21,0:16:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet our new roomma—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.88,0:16:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up with everyone? \NWe've got new roommates!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.34,0:16:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can’t believe this—\Nan eight-person dorm!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.46,0:16:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You must feel like a litter of puppies all tumbling over each other in your sleep. {?????????????????? no clue what she says or means, not in the book it seems; I hear "like puppies rolling and tumbling in their sleep" - think she means it as "you're packed tight here, like puppies in a box"}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.96,0:16:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.45,0:16:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,At our old school, \Nthe bedrooms were just doubles,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.64,0:16:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with maids doing all the cleaning.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.57,0:16:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my! Look at that, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.31,0:16:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the pillows have traces of repairs!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.87,0:16:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they make pillows out of socks. {??????????? lit: at clare, socks at pillows}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.08,0:16:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet even their textbooks look like patchwork. {lit: they even use patchwork on their textbooks, don't they}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.31,0:16:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, everyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.96,0:16:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They're asking for it! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.72,0:16:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.69,0:17:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It suits you so perfectly!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.22,0:17:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Our twin princesses!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.39,0:17:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat! Hurry to the bathroom! {lit: let's wash quickly}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.13,0:17:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Cowards! Anyone can laugh at another \Nif they set them up like that. {lit: cowards, doing silly things, laughing at others}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.17,0:17:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Your hearts are made of rags, and no stitching in the world could mend them. {lit: even if you guys stitch your kokoro, it's rags - kokoro could be both heart and soul/spirit/mind}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.65,0:17:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.24,0:17:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.36,0:17:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If you play pranks on newcomers, \Nyou play them on me! {lit: something like pranks on new students I won't forgive either}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.59,0:17:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary? Are you really willing to side with {\i1}them{\i0}?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.60,0:17:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're different from us and a bit headstrong, \Nbut they can be reasoned with if you're patient! {lit: not used to it and a bit stubborn, but if you explain properly, they'll understand}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.60,0:17:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you remember what Headmistress told us? \NYou can’t judge someone just by first impressions. {lit: only from looking a bit, judging people is not good}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.89,0:17:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay out of it, you honor student!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.83,0:17:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.23,0:17:40.26,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.86,0:17:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so fast, you!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.33,0:17:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you lived like princesses back at your old school... {omitting "in a glittering castle" for CPS}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.87,0:17:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet! Let me handle this.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.90,0:17:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Please understand—\Nhere at St. Clare’s, you take care of yourself {lit: take good care of your things}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.46,0:18:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and pull your weight with everyone else—that responsibility is as important as lessons themselves. {lit: work for everyone's sake, that sense of responsibility is about as valued as studying}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.15,0:18:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d bet you two can’t even fasten a single button by yourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.05,0:18:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not about to waste my precious youth \Non buttoning and cleaning!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.47,0:18:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! So oppressive and tight-handed—\NSt. Clare's is the worst school ever! {lit: pushy and stingy}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.66,0:18:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But aren't you forgetting something important, your highness? {ohime-sama = princess}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.94,0:18:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The point is not what you think of St. Clare’s—\Nbut what St. Clare’s thinks of you!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.03,0:18:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better not make that mistake again.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.07,0:18:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.95,0:18:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You two will never fit in with us at St. Clare's! {lit: not suited for clare at all}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.47,0:18:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What's all the ruckus?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.96,0:18:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there an argument?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.98,0:18:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.30,0:18:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen a school this uncouth! \NWhere's the headmistress's room? {/rude}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.93,0:18:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.93,0:18:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.38,0:18:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to dump on her everything \Nthat drives me crazy about St. Clare’s!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.99,0:18:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,On the headmistress?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.29,0:18:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I'll say everything I want to say!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.26,0:18:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she'll be able to.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.50,0:18:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.68,0:19:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.94,0:19:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably don't need to ask you two \Nwhat your names are.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.88,0:19:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia and Isabel. \NThe O'Sullivan twins, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.85,0:19:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.00,0:19:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, we need to talk.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.04,0:19:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.78,0:19:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You father and mother really do know you girls through and through. {?? dunno, maybe "I know everything about you from ...."}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.11,0:19:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And they love both of you deeply.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.30,0:19:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.15,0:19:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.82,0:19:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just reading a letter from your parents.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.36,0:19:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"Patricia and Isabel may rush to the headmistress' room as soon as they arrive.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.31,0:19:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat will do the talking.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.30,0:20:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When she insists on a complaint, \Nher eyes sparkle even more than usual.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.25,0:20:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Isabel will be a bit timid, thinking,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.11,0:20:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are we really doing the right thing?”,\Nwhile batting her eyelashes furiously."
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.88,0:20:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, what are we going to do now?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.82,0:20:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They ask me to scold you both \Nmercilessly in this letter.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.30,0:20:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like your parents love you \Nand want to be proud of you,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.20,0:20:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also deeply concerned \Nabout every single student at our school.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.80,0:20:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Many students have come here, just like you two,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.44,0:20:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and discovered for themselves what’s most wonderful and important while growing up at St. Clare’s. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.42,0:20:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you become rigid and close your heart to change, you won’t ever be able to notice it. {lit: you won't see anything}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.83,0:21:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Clare's is doing its best for you. {from book}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:03.83,0:21:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So please do your best to make St. Clare's proud of you in return.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.95,0:21:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.75,0:21:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you agree with her? {lit: why did you answer [yes/okay]}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.80,0:21:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How couldn't I?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.25,0:21:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt like Headmistress had seen right through me, \Nto the depths of my heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.08,0:21:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because you're so shy! {/indecisive}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.59,0:21:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You were actually close \Nto saying "Okay" yourself, weren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.50,0:21:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope, I made an oath.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.10,0:21:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.42,0:21:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't lose.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.83,0:21:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give everyone a shock—\Neven the headmistress! {/shock}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.27,0:21:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In sports, studying—everything!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.42,0:21:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll show everyone what we're capable of!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.74,0:21:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The O'Sullivan twins will be the best at this school.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.51,0:21:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I heard a voice...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.79,0:22:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Just Kathleen grinding her teeth? {involuntary nocturnal tooth grinding; bruxism - no clue how you can mistake that for a voice}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.22,0:22:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Just you watch, \Nthe real show only starts now.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.56,0:22:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be in awe when they see our real abilities. {lit: when they see our real capability, they'll scream "I'm beaten/I give up"}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:12.03,0:22:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll unleash a "twin shock" on St. Clare's! {sensation; commotion; hullabaloo​}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.83,0:23:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.78,0:23:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.15,0:23:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This girl, Belinda, from the fifth form suddenly summoned us. What might she need?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.82,0:23:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,For you to clean her shoes, \Nlight the stove and boil some water.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.04,0:23:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we refuse, they'll forbid us from going out—you think that's acceptable?!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.12,0:23:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider it a custom of St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.33,0:23:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't care to follow \NSt. Clare's stupid ways. Right, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.86,0:23:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:56.64,0:23:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.07,0:23:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at my Lacrosse! {見て! 私のラクロス}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.67,0:24:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
Comment: 0,0:24:01.17,0:24:04.17,Song,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.47,0:02:33.02,Song,,0,0,0,,If only there were no tests,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.02,0:02:36.74,Song,,0,0,0,,School would've been a fun place for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.74,0:02:43.08,Song,,0,0,0,,I never cared much for studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.18,0:02:51.59,Song,,0,0,0,,I just stared out the window all through class,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.59,0:02:57.63,Song,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,200)}Always dreaming away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.26,0:03:05.57,Song,,0,0,0,,But if I'd at least taken English seriously,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.67,0:03:12.91,Song,,0,0,0,,By now I'd be some cool international girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.88,0:03:20.45,Song,,0,0,0,,Better to study a little than not at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:26.02,Song,,0,0,0,,There must be at least one thing you're good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.59,0:03:35.60,Song,,0,0,0,,Better to study while you still have the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.60,0:03:41.24,Song,,0,0,0,,Realizing too late won't help you then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.33,0:22:39.08,Song,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget, looking up at the sky from this hilltop,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.08,0:22:47.55,Song,,0,0,0,,The morning sun so beautiful, on spring days, just us two.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.52,0:22:55.74,Song,,0,0,0,,All the hardships and the sorrows,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.17,0:22:53.84,Song,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.11,0:23:00.11,Song,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.69,0:23:03.90,Song,,0,0,0,,Carry them away gently from this hilltop,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:10.81,Song,,0,0,0,,together with the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.81,0:23:21.25,Song,,0,0,0,,This vast, blue sky—may it never change,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.25,0:23:30.83,Song,,0,0,0,,And may my dearest friends stay just the way they are.
